description:
Digital chapters for the Continuum graphic novel.

Historian David Marcus spent his entire life studying one single day. In 2010, the prime minister of Israel was assassinated in what was dubbed the "Longest Day in History." The events that followed were linear, ominous and unstoppable as the nuclear weapons were launched. Life existed for decades before a major break through occurred. After years of looking to the stars for a new planet, scientists found that is was possible for one-way time travel through a rift in our solar system. Instead of finding a new world, what if a team was able to stop the "Longest Day in History?" What if we could go back in time to save our planet?
name: Continuum

description:
Twenty years ago a young couple, Wendy and Richard Pini, discovered within themselves an intense desire to tell a story with stirring words and beautiful pictures. Theirs would be the tale of a tribe of elves—brave Cutter and his loyal WolfRiders—seeking and finding a home in a hostile world. Unable to interest established publishers in their dream, the two began self-publishing "ElfQuest" the comic book, armed with little business experience but also the strong urge to learn by doing.

Two decades later, "ElfQuest" is still going strong—as a comic book series, bestselling graphic novels, prose adaptations, music, and more. To celebrate, WolfRider Books is pleased to participate in a multinational "ElfFest"—an anniversary magazine containing never-before published material, including a brand-new ElfQuest story written and drawn by Wendy Pini exclusively for this publication!
name: ElfQuest: The First 20 Years

deck: French Manga series. The title has no meaning in english but refers to the french expression nanar. A nanar is a so poorly realized and ridiculous work of art (usually a movie) it becomes unintentionally funny and comical.
description: Chance, Xiong Mao and Ombre are three students, who enrolled at the Faculté des Études Académiques des Héros (FEAH) (Faculty of Academic Studies of Heroes), a university that trains superheroes. At the beginning of the academic year the students are grouped in teams of three, and the three end up together because no one else wants them in their team, due to their low grades on the entarnce exams. Bound by the rejection of the other students (and professors) they form a strong friendship. Between courses on strategy, history of superheroes and workshops on cultivating a public image or choosing the right superhero-outfit, they encounter numerous difficulties with the management of the university and some of their fellow students. After some issues with their respective lodgings, they live together in on old tower that they restored on campus. Only one professor, Funérailles, takes a liking to them and decides to give them a hand when needed. The complete cycle will compromise 7 issues.
name: Freaks' Squeele

description:
Trade paperback collecting Avengelyne.

Imagine if all you knew your entire life was the magic of Heaven.

Days that never end, streets paved with gold, pearly gates, eternal life, no sorrow, no pain.

Then one day, it all came to an abrupt end.

Everything you ever new was taken from you and you were exiled to an alien world.

A world you knew nothing about.

A world where you would fight for your survival against the temptations that threaten to destroy you.

Welcome to the world of Avengelyne.

Vengeance has a new name!
name: Avengelyne
